786610 275No person to be a director of more than twenty companies. After the commencement of this Act, no person shall, save as otherwise provided in section 276, hold office at the same time as director in more than twenty companies.
577542 276 Choice to be made by director of more than twenty companies at commencement of Act.
1007210 1Any person holding office as director in more than twenty companies immediately before the commencement of this Act shall, within two months from such commencement,-
760135 achoose not more than twenty of those companies, as companies in which he wishes to continue to hold the office of director;
1774108 bresign his office as director in the other companies; and
1479233 cintimate the choice made by him under clause (a) to each of the companies in which he was holding the office of director before such commencement, to the Registrar having jurisdiction in respect of each such company, and also to the Central Government.
547583 2Any resignation made in pursuance of clause (b) of sub- section (1) shall become effective immediately on the despatch thereof to the company concerned.
1777835 3No such person shall act as director-
1844845 ain more than twenty companies, after the expiry of two months from the commencement of this Act; or
1807009 bof any company after despatching the resignation of his office as director thereof, in pursuance of clause (b) of sub- section (1).
